Below is a safe-order checklist that removes every resource we created without hitting dependency errors.
 (Everything is done in the AWS Console UI; the service names are the ones we used in the blog.)

ğŸ”‘ Golden Rule
Delete from the inside-out:
ECS (tasks â†’ services â†’ cluster)


Load-balancing stuff (target group â†’ ALB)


Compute-related networking (NAT, IGW, ENIs, EIPs)


Core VPC objects (route tables â†’ subnets â†’ security groups â†’ VPC)



1 . ECS / Fargate
1-A Stop & delete the services
Console âœ ECS â†’ Clusters


Click twotier_cluster âœ Services tab


For each service (twotier-service-flask, twotier-service-sql)


Actions â†’ Delete âœ type delete âœ Delete


Wait ~30 s until the Tasks tab shows 0 Running / 0 Pending.
1-B Delete the cluster
Still on Clusters list âœ Tick twotier_cluster âœ Delete cluster âœ type delete âœ Delete
1-C (Optional) Deregister task definitions
ECS â†’ Task definitions âœ open each (twotier_task_flask, twotier_task_sql) âœ
 Actions â†’ Deregister (repeat for all revisions).
 (Not billed, but keeps console tidy.)

2 . Load Balancer & Target Group
2-A Delete Target Group
EC2 â†’ Target Groups âœ select twotier-flask-tg âœ Actions â†’ Delete âœ Delete
2-B Delete ALB
EC2 â†’ Load Balancers âœ select twotier-alb âœ Actions â†’ Delete âœ Delete

3 . Networking Edge Resources
3-A Delete NAT Gateway & release Elastic IP
VPC â†’ NAT Gateways âœ select twotier-nat âœ Actions â†’ Delete âœ Delete


Note the Elastic IP address shown, then:
 EC2 â†’ Elastic IP addresses âœ tick the same EIP âœ Actions â†’ Release âœ Release


(Must wait ~1 min until NAT status = deleted before you can delete private route.)
3-B Detach & delete Internet Gateway
VPC â†’ Internet Gateways âœ select twotier-igw
 Actions â†’ Detach from VPC âœ confirm âœ Actions â†’ Delete âœ Delete

4 . Route Tables
VPC â†’ Route Tables


Delete twotier-private-rt first (no edge dependencies)
 Select âœ Actions â†’ Delete âœ confirm


Delete twotier-public-rt next.



5 . Subnets
VPC â†’ Subnets âœ
 Delete in any order:
Subnet name
Private-Subnet-1
Private-Subnet-2
Public-Subnet-1
Public-Subnet-2

(Select âœ Actions â†’ Delete subnet âœ confirm)

6 . Security Groups (custom ones)
EC2 â†’ Security Groups
Delete the three you created (they are now unused):
alb-sg


flask-sg


mysql-sg


(tick âœ Actions â†’ Delete security group)

7 . Delete the VPC
VPC â†’ Your VPCs âœ select twotier-vpc âœ Actions â†’ Delete VPC âœ confirm.
AWS automatically removes any remaining DHCP options set or route-table stubs.

8 . (Optional) House-keeping
Resource
Console Path
Action
CloudWatch Log groups
CloudWatch â†’ Logs â†’ Log groups
delete /ecs/twotier_task_flask & /ecs/twotier_task_sql
ECR repos (if you pushed images)
ECR â†’ Repositories
delete repo
